@RonnyPfannschmidt: I updated some tests which didn't use `from_parent`.

@bluetech: I had to suppress the MINUS_K_COLON and MINUS_K_DASH warnings because they would turn into errors in 6.0, and we want to make them into errors in 7.0 only, given they were added too recently; we should reintroduce the warnings in 6.1 ( (https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7361). 

Closes #5584

body:
@RonnyPfannschmidt I just realized something.

The plan here is to have a function somewhat like this:

```python
def deprecated(reason: str, *, due: int, stacklevel: int):
    if due >= pytest version [0]:
        warnings.warn(PytestExpiredDeprecationWarning(reason), stacklevel=stacklevel)
    else:
        warnings.warn(PytestDeprecationWarning(reason), stacklevel=stacklevel)
```

Usage:

```python
def use_of_deprecated_thing():
   deprecated("don't use this function, use X instead", due=7)
   # do its thing
```

However, because our version depends on the tag of the release, the actual pytest version will stay `6.X` until the actual tag `7.0.0` is pushed at release time, and in *that moment* that function will issue `PytestExpiredDeprecationWarning`, which will then break the actual release. Any ideas?

Remember the stacklevel for warnings.warn:

```
def deprecated(reason: str, *, due: int, stacklevel=0):
    stacklevel = stacklevel + 1
    if due >= pytest version [0]:
        warnings.warn(PytestExpiredDeprecationWarning(reason), stacklevel=stacklevel)
    else:
        warnings.warn(PytestDeprecationWarning(reason), stacklevel=stacklevel)
```

> I strongly oppose combining declaration and triggering of warnings

Noted, just to get this out of the way then:

```python
def deprecated_warning(reason: str, *, due: int) -> PytestWarning:
    if due >= pytest version [0]:
        return PytestExpiredDeprecationWarning(reason)
    else:
        return PytestDeprecationWarning(reason)
```

> @nicoddemus if the next guessed version is based on semver + towncrier inference, it's 7.0.dev... As soon as a breaking change is merged

Ahh I see, thanks. 

Should we hold this issue until that happens then?
